import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="API testing training — grimbergIT"
  description="API testing workshops — the layer that quietly carries the weight of a delivery pipeline."
>
  <article class="surface">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workshop · 04</p>
    <h1>API Testing</h1>

    <p>
      The API layer is the one carrying most of the risk in a modern application, and the one whose
      tests get the least love. This workshop is for teams whose end-to-end suite has grown into a
      proxy for missing API checks — and who want to unpick that.
    </p>

    <h2>What we cover</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Where API tests belong in a suite, and where they don't.</li>
      <li>Contract testing — consumer-driven and provider-driven, with the trade-offs of each.</li>
      <li>Schema validation as a first-class citizen, not an afterthought.</li>
      <li>
        Authentication flows: OAuth, session cookies, service accounts, and how to test them without
        brittle setup.
      </li>
      <li>
        How to layer API tests so the browser-level checks stop bearing weight they shouldn't.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Format</h2>
    <p>
      One day by default. Splittable into two half-days if the team's calendar prefers it. Also
      available as a multi-week cohort. Tooling-agnostic — we work in whatever your team is already
      using (Postman, Playwright, Cypress, REST-assured, supertest, curl scripts).
    </p>

    <h2>What you leave with</h2>
    <p>
      A concrete plan for where API tests fit in your suite, at least one contract in place between
      two of your services, and a written recap on which tests to move where.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/training/">← Back to training</a> ·
      <a href="/contact">Book a session →</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
